UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1830
1 graduate card at the time of purchase, and the exemption shall extend
2 to the PGA graduate and one (1) guest.
3 3. As used in this paragraph, "PGA HOPE program" means the Helping
4 Our Patriots Everywhere program established by the Professional
5 Golfers' Association of America's Reach Foundation, which
6 introduces and teaches golf to veterans and active-duty military to
7 enhance their physical, mental, social, and emotional well-being.
8 (5) The Department of Parks is authorized to enter into any agreement with the Breaks
9 Interstate Park Commission for the operation of any facilities in the Breaks
10 Interstate Park.
11 (6) The Department of Parks is authorized to accept, for deposit in a trust and agency
12 fund account in accordance with KRS 45.253, on behalf of the state any grant or
13 contribution, federal or otherwise, to assist in meeting the cost of carrying out the
14 functions assigned to the Department of Parks.
15 (7) Notwithstanding any provision in KRS Chapter 41, 45, 45A, or 47 to the contrary,
16 there may be established separate cash funds and depositories at each state park
17 from which immediate payment of refunds may be made to a patron or guest of
18 such state park of any unearned money advanced or paid by such guest or patron.
19 The department may accept from a guest or patron an amount which includes the
20 fee for the service rendered plus a gratuity for the waitress or other designated
21 person and remit the gratuity directly from the depository or cash fund to the
22 designated recipient thereof. Such funds or depositories shall be governed by
23 regulations established by the Department of Parks and approved by the Finance
24 and Administration Cabinet.
25 (8) The commissioner may promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with
26 provisions of KRS Chapter 13A in order to carry out the provisions of this section.
